<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-03T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-03T06:44:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.635 Neep/22: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-03T11:00:00-00:44">December 3, 1937—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 3—9:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>66. Neep Agreement ratified by the Legislature. President empowered
                                to settle controversial points at issue, such as sliding scale of
                                from 4 to 6 cents royalty and additional royalty on all other
                                minerals mined apart from iron.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>